The Department shall:
Coordinate with other State agencies, federal agencies, other states, local governments, and interested persons in the regulation of nontidal wetlands;
Assist local governments in undertaking nontidal wetland management planning, including mapping, technical assistance, and expediting the permit process;
Develop certification programs to ensure uniform and professional standards for the identification, delineation, functional assessment, and mitigation of nontidal wetlands;
Evaluate proposed activities on nontidal wetlands and grant or deny permits or other approvals of proposed activities;
Conduct watershed studies and educational programs and disseminate information concerning the nontidal wetlands program;
Prepare, adopt, and periodically revise guidance maps of nontidal wetlands;
Adopt standards for planning, regulating, restoring, creating, and enhancing nontidal wetlands;
Purchase, restore, and create nontidal wetlands; and
Conduct periodic monitoring, cumulative impact assessment, and evaluation of activities authorized under this subtitle.
